article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 70, Cal Poly-SLO 68
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Jacques Streeter made a 15-foot running bank shot at the buzzer to lift Cal State Fullerton to a 70-68 victory against Cal Poly-San Luis Obispo on Wednesday night. Streeter had 21 points for the Titans (15-12, 8-6 Big West), who won their fifth straight road game and fifth in a row overall. Shawn Lewis had 19 points for Cal Poly (10-17, 6-8) and made a 3-pointer to tie the score with 5.2 seconds remaining. Streeter gave Fullerton a 66-65 advantage on a 3-pointer with 1:32 remaining, and Gerard Anderson, who had 17 points and nine rebounds, extended the lead with a pair of free throws with 39 seconds to play. Lewis had 11 rebounds. David Hanson had 17 points and nine rebounds for the Mustangs.
